gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Clippers 113, Warriors 112
gameRecap.excerpt: Paul George made a 3PT field goal with 8.9 seconds left in the 4th quarter to give the Clippers their first lead of the game, 113-112, and held on for the final seconds to defeat the Warriors, 113-112. Paul George led Los Angeles with 25 points, six rebounds, and six assists as James Harden (21 points, five rebounds, nine assists) and Kawhi Leonard (20 points, eight rebounds, seven assists) totaled 41 points. Stephen Curry led the Warriors with 22 points and a season-high 11 assists while Draymond Green added 21 points, nine rebounds, and four assists. The Clippers improve to 9-10 as the Warriors move to 9-11 on the year.
